9
00:00:29,696 --> 00:00:31,869
<i>If you have a voice,
we want to hear it.</i>

10
00:00:32,032 --> 00:00:35,582
<i>Come on down and see if you can
knock Big Black off his block.</i>

11
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:10,487
Come on.
I wrote this one just for you.

12
00:01:10,654 --> 00:01:12,782
I don't know why I let you
talk me into coming.

13
00:01:12,948 --> 00:01:14,950
I think I'm the oldest sardine
in this can.

14
00:01:15,117 --> 00:01:17,495
- Well, you don't look it.
- Well, that's true.

15
00:01:17,661 --> 00:01:19,584
But it's your song.
You go up and sing it.

16
00:01:19,746 --> 00:01:22,340
- You're the singer in our family.
- Honey, you sing.

17
00:01:23,083 --> 00:01:25,882
Yeah, but you know
how to hold people's attention.

18
00:01:26,878 --> 00:01:28,505
People love to just hear you talk.

19
00:01:28,672 --> 00:01:31,471
Imagine how you're gonna knock it out
when you get up there.

20
00:01:55,949 --> 00:01:57,622
All right, now.

21
00:01:59,828 --> 00:02:03,082
Fellas. Fellas.

22
00:02:03,248 --> 00:02:04,295
Nice.

23
00:02:04,458 --> 00:02:05,926
Keep that applause going.

24
00:02:06,084 --> 00:02:08,337
Give it up one more time for Black.

25
00:02:08,503 --> 00:02:11,222
If you guys are having a good time,
say "oh, yeah."

26
00:02:11,381 --> 00:02:12,428
Oh, yeah!

27
00:02:12,591 --> 00:02:14,685
Please.
I went over everything with the band.

28
00:02:16,345 --> 00:02:20,316
Please. I just want
to hear my song. Please.

29
00:02:20,974 --> 00:02:23,477
Are you sure you want to do this?

30
00:02:23,644 --> 00:02:26,739
- You, are you sure?
- That man is Black!

31
00:02:26,897 --> 00:02:28,023
You hear that?

32
00:02:28,190 --> 00:02:30,693
That's the sound of success, baby.

33
00:02:30,859 --> 00:02:32,281
What you doing?

34
00:02:32,444 --> 00:02:33,991
Wait a minute.

35
00:02:34,154 --> 00:02:35,201
Let's get a room.

36
00:02:36,990 --> 00:02:38,708
Wait a minute. Bro, you see her?

37
00:02:38,867 --> 00:02:41,370
Good God, woman.
What's wrong with you?

38
00:02:41,536 --> 00:02:44,289
Coming up to the stage right now
is a beautiful young lady.

39
00:02:44,456 --> 00:02:46,879
She's just as fine as she wants to be.

40
00:02:47,042 --> 00:02:49,215
Now, this lady is a Detroit native...

41
00:02:49,378 --> 00:02:51,881
...and she's never been
to the Discovery Club...

42
00:02:52,047 --> 00:02:55,392
...so I want everybody
to show her some extra love.

43
00:02:55,550 --> 00:02:58,895
Strutting up on-stage right now...

44
00:02:59,054 --> 00:03:03,434
...is Sister Anderson!

45
00:03:07,396 --> 00:03:08,443
Thank you.

46
00:03:42,431 --> 00:03:44,183
So, what's up, Mr. Manager?

47
00:03:44,349 --> 00:03:46,477
We gonna do some business or what?

48
00:03:46,643 --> 00:03:48,520
Black, you got to lose
some weight, baby.

49
00:03:48,687 --> 00:03:51,315
Man, you must be crazy.
Man, all the ladies love me.

50
00:03:51,481 --> 00:03:55,236
And besides, this old belly
is what helps me sing.

51
00:03:56,194 --> 00:03:57,912
TV's getting bigger-

52
00:03:58,071 --> 00:03:59,823
- Clothes getting smaller.
- Yeah.

53
00:03:59,990 --> 00:04:03,620
- You know, you'd be good on radio.
- Man, that's cold, man. That's cold.

54
00:04:14,212 --> 00:04:16,260
Lord have mercy!

55
00:05:08,350 --> 00:05:09,602
All right.

56
00:05:09,768 --> 00:05:11,987
I see you looking. Sure, you're right.

57
00:05:12,145 --> 00:05:14,989
You were so great.
But we have to hurry.

58
00:05:15,148 --> 00:05:16,946
We have five minutes
to catch the bus.

59
00:05:17,108 --> 00:05:19,861
Give it up one more time
for Sister Anderson.

60
00:05:20,028 --> 00:05:21,405
My goodness gracious.

61
00:05:21,571 --> 00:05:23,539
Excuse me. Excuse me.

62
00:05:23,698 --> 00:05:25,120
It's Sister, right?

63
00:05:25,283 --> 00:05:28,833
You gotta forgive me for earlier.
I was all wrong about you.

64
00:05:28,995 --> 00:05:32,124
You were foxy up there.
Promise me you'll come back next week.

65
00:05:32,791 --> 00:05:35,044
Maybe. Maybe not.

66
00:05:35,210 --> 00:05:37,929
- But, baby, I gotta...
- Excuse me. Excuse me.

67
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:40,473
I really don't date younger men.

68
00:05:40,632 --> 00:05:44,057
- No, no, please, you were so--
- I'm sorry, but we have to go.

69
00:05:44,219 --> 00:05:46,563
Where can I find you?

70
00:05:52,936 --> 00:05:55,064
Next time it's your turn.

71
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:57,073
Hi.

72
00:05:59,526 --> 00:06:01,824
Hi. Thank you.

73
00:06:02,863 --> 00:06:05,241
You were so good.

74
00:06:12,873 --> 00:06:14,500
That was so fun!

75
00:06:14,666 --> 00:06:16,464
Yeah, it was.

76
00:06:16,626 --> 00:06:19,926
Next time, can you get through
the chorus before you do your solo?

77
00:06:20,088 --> 00:06:21,385
Miss Thing, next time?

78
00:06:21,548 --> 00:06:23,642
Yeah. I have a lot more songs.

79
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:27,225
Then you better get a lot more confident
and learn to sing them yourself.

80
00:06:27,387 --> 00:06:28,684
Slavery is over.

81
00:06:28,847 --> 00:06:30,724
Really? You're not gonna
sing anymore?

82
00:06:30,891 --> 00:06:32,689
No.

83
00:06:34,477 --> 00:06:36,696
Assume the position. What?

84
00:07:05,842 --> 00:07:09,767
Y'all are late, and she's up.

85
00:07:22,317 --> 00:07:24,490
- Sparkle. Hush.
- Sorry.

86
00:07:32,494 --> 00:07:34,622
Hurry.

87
00:07:37,123 --> 00:07:39,376
What y'all doing in there?

88
00:07:50,679 --> 00:07:52,647
My babies.

89
00:07:53,056 --> 00:07:55,354
But I know y'all don't
love each other that much.

90
00:07:56,351 --> 00:07:58,524
Sister and Sparkle, curl your hair.

91
00:07:58,687 --> 00:08:00,689
Church in the morning.

92
00:08:00,855 --> 00:08:01,902
You hear me?

93
00:08:02,774 --> 00:08:06,244
Dolores, why is my window open?
I'm not trying to heat the outside.

94
00:08:08,363 --> 00:08:09,580
Close it.

95
00:08:09,739 --> 00:08:11,286
- Good night.
- Good night.

96
00:08:14,119 --> 00:08:15,712
Is she gone?

97
00:08:15,870 --> 00:08:19,875
Y'all heifers sneak out,
and I get fussed at?

98
00:08:20,542 --> 00:08:22,544
Laugh at-- Laugh at that.
Is that funny?

99
00:08:22,919 --> 00:08:24,216
Peace be with you.

100
00:08:24,379 --> 00:08:27,132
And also with you.

101
00:08:30,051 --> 00:08:33,021
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

102
00:08:33,179 --> 00:08:39,027
You know, the Lord loves a church
full of happy, good-looking black folk.

103
00:08:39,185 --> 00:08:40,562
Amen!

104
00:08:40,729 --> 00:08:42,572
I know y'all happy
this morning, right?

105
00:08:42,731 --> 00:08:43,823
Yes!

106
00:08:43,982 --> 00:08:47,907
Ain't no frowns in this
church today, is there?

107
00:08:48,653 --> 00:08:51,702
No frowns, no clowns,
not in church.

108
00:08:51,865 --> 00:08:53,458
And look at the choir.

109
00:08:53,616 --> 00:08:55,914
- How y'all doing this morning?
- Good!

110
00:08:56,077 --> 00:08:58,375
- Levi, there she go.
- What? What?

111
00:08:58,538 --> 00:09:01,712
Seven Sundays, seven churches,
and $7 later, and I find her.

112
00:09:01,875 --> 00:09:03,468
- That light-skinned girl?
- There.

113
00:09:03,626 --> 00:09:05,674
Oh, man.
Well, that's Tammy Anderson.

114
00:09:05,837 --> 00:09:08,386
Yeah, man, she is smoking hot.

115
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:10,175
- Tammy.
- Two sisters. They all fine.

116
00:09:10,341 --> 00:09:12,093
- They can all sing too.
- Is that right?

117
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:14,979
Sure, you're right.
But they mama crazy, though.

118
00:09:17,182 --> 00:09:19,776
Y'all know better.

119
00:09:19,934 --> 00:09:23,734
I know I can't sing,
but I can love to hear singing.

120
00:09:23,897 --> 00:09:25,149
'Yes!
'Right?

121
00:09:28,193 --> 00:09:31,618
I'll see you next week, right?
Okay. See you later.

122
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:36,956
Excuse me. You was at the Discovery
a few weeks ago.

123
00:09:43,374 --> 00:09:46,878
- Bible study's at your house this week?
- Yeah, it is.

124
00:09:47,045 --> 00:09:48,422
You know, you bad at this.

125
00:09:50,131 --> 00:09:51,974
Just act natural.

126
00:09:52,842 --> 00:09:54,139
Hi. My name's Stix.

127
00:09:54,302 --> 00:09:55,599
Sparkle.

128
00:09:56,221 --> 00:09:57,564
Sara.

129
00:09:57,722 --> 00:10:01,147
- Who is my baby talking to?
- Nineteen ain't no baby no more, Emma.

130
00:10:02,352 --> 00:10:05,231
What? No need in eyeballing me.
I tells the truth.

131
00:10:05,396 --> 00:10:07,023
It's in my contract as your friend.

132
00:10:07,565 --> 00:10:09,988
I'm telling you,
you hold on too tight to that one...

133
00:10:10,151 --> 00:10:12,995
...she'll be unmarried
and back on your doorstep like Sister.

134
00:10:14,322 --> 00:10:16,120
That's just temporary, okay?

135
00:10:16,282 --> 00:10:19,206
Well, New York just spit her
right on back out, huh?

136
00:10:19,369 --> 00:10:20,495
- No.
- You know what?

137
00:10:20,662 --> 00:10:23,336
You worry about your daughter,
I'll worry about mine.

138
00:10:23,498 --> 00:10:25,171
- I'm just saying.
- Yeah, what?

139
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:26,710
- Mom, I need some money.
- What?

140
00:10:26,876 --> 00:10:29,675
They selling dinners in the basement,
and they going fast.

141
00:10:29,838 --> 00:10:30,885
- Mom?
- Don't do it.

142
00:10:31,047 --> 00:10:32,674
- Mama, please.
- Come with me.

143
00:10:32,841 --> 00:10:34,969
- Now you stop.
- See y'all later.

144
00:10:42,016 --> 00:10:44,018
Sparkle.

145
00:10:44,185 --> 00:10:45,732
Let's go.

146
00:10:46,563 --> 00:10:50,534
So I will see you
at Bible study, Sparkle?

147
00:10:51,734 --> 00:10:53,327
Maybe.

148
00:11:03,788 --> 00:11:06,883
<i>Another one of my white friends
came to me the other day and said:</i>

149
00:11:07,041 --> 00:11:09,715
<i>"Where's the best place
to hide something from a Negro...</i>

150
00:11:09,878 --> 00:11:11,255
<i>...and he'll never find it?"</i>

151
00:11:11,421 --> 00:11:13,640
<i>I told him, "A work boot. "</i>

152
00:11:16,384 --> 00:11:18,182
Y'all know he talking about us, right?

153
00:11:18,344 --> 00:11:19,812
<i>People are always asking me...</i>

154
00:11:20,555 --> 00:11:22,148
- Where is she?
- I don't know.

155
00:11:22,640 --> 00:11:26,270
- Ms. Anderson, where's the bathroom?
- Down the hall, second door to the right.

156
00:11:26,436 --> 00:11:27,562
Second door.

157
00:11:27,729 --> 00:11:29,231
- Thank you.
- Yeah, second door.

158
00:11:29,856 --> 00:11:33,736
<i>Ladies and gentlemen, Satin Struthers.
Let's give him a hand.</i>

159
00:11:33,902 --> 00:11:36,997
<i>Great job. Thanks for coming.
Isn't he funny?</i>

160
00:11:39,699 --> 00:11:40,746
There you are.

161
00:11:41,409 --> 00:11:43,457
Why you not in Bible study?

162
00:11:43,620 --> 00:11:45,122
Haven't you heard?

163
00:11:45,288 --> 00:11:48,508
I'm a heathen. Don't want to sit in there
and be a hypocrite.

164
00:11:48,666 --> 00:11:50,634
Well, we already
got something in common...

165
00:11:50,793 --> 00:11:54,388
...because I only came
just so I could ask you out.

166
00:11:56,341 --> 00:11:59,094
The other door. To the right.

167
00:11:59,260 --> 00:12:01,729
Other door. Sorry.

168
00:12:10,647 --> 00:12:13,116
Oh, y'all like that, huh?

169
00:12:13,274 --> 00:12:16,323
Funky dance, huh? You like that.
You like that music? Funky, huh?

170
00:12:17,111 --> 00:12:18,954
It make you want to dance.
Come on.

171
00:12:19,113 --> 00:12:20,239
Get it, Mama.

172
00:12:20,406 --> 00:12:21,498
Yeah, Mama gonna get it.

173
00:12:21,658 --> 00:12:22,875
Mama gonna get it.

174
00:12:23,034 --> 00:12:24,627
And you will too.

175
00:12:24,786 --> 00:12:27,915
You keep dancing like that,
you'll bring home a baby you can't feed.

176
00:12:29,123 --> 00:12:30,170
Let's open our Bibles.

177
00:12:32,627 --> 00:12:36,097
The deal was color television
for an hour of Bible study.

178
00:12:36,798 --> 00:12:39,642
I lived up to my end,
now you live up to yours.

179
00:12:40,635 --> 00:12:42,729
So let's go to Psalms 10--

180
00:12:42,887 --> 00:12:46,312
Reverend Bryce called.
Says he need you to check the books.

181
00:12:46,474 --> 00:12:49,648
The numbers are not adding up.

182
00:12:52,313 --> 00:12:53,940
All right.

183
00:12:57,819 --> 00:12:59,241
What are you watching?

184
00:13:01,990 --> 00:13:04,869
Oh, I love this song.

185
00:13:11,791 --> 00:13:14,761
No, no. Too many hormones
unattended in here.

186
00:13:14,919 --> 00:13:17,763
Let's go. Get out. Come on.
Sister, turn that TV off.

187
00:13:17,922 --> 00:13:20,220
Thank you. Come on, let's go.

188
00:13:20,383 --> 00:13:21,851
- Bye, Sparkle.
- See you.

189
00:13:22,010 --> 00:13:25,059
- Good night, Mama.
- Good night, baby.

190
00:13:25,221 --> 00:13:27,098
It was just getting good.

191
00:13:27,265 --> 00:13:28,608
See you tonight, Sparkle.

192
00:13:28,766 --> 00:13:31,315
- Call you later.
- All right.

193
00:13:31,477 --> 00:13:32,820
See you next time.

194
00:13:32,979 --> 00:13:35,448
- Bye, Tammy.
- Bye, Tune.

195
00:13:38,192 --> 00:13:40,570
Well, good night.

196
00:13:40,737 --> 00:13:42,410
Good night.

197
00:13:47,744 --> 00:13:51,749
Why are all the cute ones
always so stupid?

198
00:13:52,498 --> 00:13:55,126
Hey, can I talk to you for a second?

199
00:14:03,634 --> 00:14:06,012
All right, I'm going.

200
00:15:22,255 --> 00:15:23,598
Please, don't stop.

201
00:15:23,756 --> 00:15:26,179
- What are you still doing here?
- That was beautiful.

202
00:15:29,303 --> 00:15:31,146
Wait, that's your song?
You wrote that?

203
00:15:31,305 --> 00:15:32,978
Only if you thought it was good.

204
00:15:33,141 --> 00:15:34,484
I thought it was phenomenal.

205
00:15:34,642 --> 00:15:36,895
Then I wrote it.

206
00:15:37,061 --> 00:15:39,564
So did you write that song
your sister sang...

207
00:15:39,730 --> 00:15:42,199
...at the Discovery a few weeks back?

208
00:15:43,192 --> 00:15:46,412
- Yes, but she kind of made it her own.
- Wait a minute.

209
00:15:46,571 --> 00:15:48,323
You wrote that song?

210
00:15:48,489 --> 00:15:50,537
You wrote the song you were singing?

211
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:53,954
You wrote the songs in here too?

212
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:56,168
Yes.

213
00:15:56,330 --> 00:15:58,173
What you gonna do with the music?

214
00:15:58,332 --> 00:16:00,334
- Nothing.
- Why not?

215
00:16:01,127 --> 00:16:03,846
Because my mother
would never let me.

216
00:16:04,005 --> 00:16:07,555
Plus, I'm not the singer in the family.
Sister is, then Dee.

217
00:16:07,717 --> 00:16:10,266
I sing in the choir
so I don't sit by myself in church.

218
00:16:10,428 --> 00:16:12,772
No offense,
but I'm just hearing excuses.

219
00:16:12,930 --> 00:16:14,603
- Excuse me?
- I don't mean to be rude.

220
00:16:14,765 --> 00:16:17,769
I'm just passionate,
especially when it comes down to music.

221
00:16:17,935 --> 00:16:20,688
That's why I'm here.
I'm staying with my cousin, Levi.

222
00:16:20,855 --> 00:16:24,155
I'm from Kansas City.
We got a cool jazz scene down there.

223
00:16:24,317 --> 00:16:27,742
I managed a few acts,
but the money's here in Motown.

224
00:16:27,904 --> 00:16:29,998
And I want to be--
I am the next Berry Gordy.

225
00:16:30,156 --> 00:16:32,705
I figure, his stomach ain't
growling like mine anymore.

226
00:16:32,867 --> 00:16:36,246
Maybe he's leaving a lot
of steak and potatoes out there.

227
00:16:37,872 --> 00:16:39,795
You mind if I hear that song again?

228
00:16:42,627 --> 00:16:44,800
Still needs a lot of work.

229
00:17:00,061 --> 00:17:01,483
Why won't you unpack?

230
00:17:01,646 --> 00:17:03,648
I really don't plan on
being here that long.

231
00:17:04,315 --> 00:17:05,908
You said that two months ago.

232
00:17:09,654 --> 00:17:11,406
Sorry

233
00:17:12,532 --> 00:17:16,958
Hey, don't ever be sorry
for telling the truth, Spark.

234
00:17:18,079 --> 00:17:19,831
What was that?

235
00:17:25,503 --> 00:17:27,301
Your Romeo is out there.

236
00:17:27,463 --> 00:17:29,340
What?

237
00:17:44,105 --> 00:17:46,449
You can't be throwing rocks
at my window.

238
00:17:46,607 --> 00:17:47,779
My mother has a gun.

239
00:17:49,652 --> 00:17:51,620
A gun. A big one.

240
00:17:51,779 --> 00:17:53,781
There's an underground club tonight.

241
00:17:53,948 --> 00:17:56,042
The kind that songwriters
don't want to miss.

242
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:57,747
You got to hear the music.

243
00:17:57,910 --> 00:18:00,288
It's the stuff they ain't playing
on the radio.

244
00:18:00,454 --> 00:18:04,004
- Come with me.
- He wants me to go hear music with him.

245
00:18:05,001 --> 00:18:08,471
You've snuck out
of the house for less.

