00:40:33,181 --> 00:40:37,061
- You finally hit that note, Sister.
- They didn't come to hear me sing, honey.

491
00:40:37,226 --> 00:40:40,321
We need more money,
or you need to book us at a better club.

492
00:40:40,480 --> 00:40:42,983
I know what you need
before you know.

493
00:40:45,193 --> 00:40:47,992
Mr. Manager, that was out of sight.

494
00:40:48,154 --> 00:40:51,374
Sparkle, I didn't know you had it like that.
And, Dee, you were good.

495
00:40:51,532 --> 00:40:54,752
- Okay.
- But you... You.

496
00:40:54,911 --> 00:40:56,379
Sister, you were on fire.

497
00:40:56,537 --> 00:40:58,756
You'll mess up my lipstick.

498
00:40:58,915 --> 00:41:01,668
Yeah, well, as much as I want
to mess up your lipstick...

499
00:41:01,834 --> 00:41:03,552
...I gotta go to work.

500
00:41:03,711 --> 00:41:05,258
Since when you working
the graveyard shift?

501
00:41:05,421 --> 00:41:08,595
Since I got a woman
that's got needs, cousin. Look at her.

502
00:41:12,220 --> 00:41:13,392
Satin.

503
00:41:13,554 --> 00:41:15,682
- Didn't know you was still in the house.
- Yeah.

504
00:41:15,848 --> 00:41:18,818
Let me introduce you to my family.
This is Sparkle. This is Dee.

505
00:41:18,977 --> 00:41:21,446
- This is Satin Struthers.
- Pleased to meet you.

506
00:41:21,604 --> 00:41:24,448
- Pleased to meet you.
- Hi.

507
00:41:24,607 --> 00:41:28,487
- And over here, in this corner, this is--
- We know each other.

508
00:41:30,446 --> 00:41:33,325
Well, first, I'd like to congratulate you
on your performance.

509
00:41:33,491 --> 00:41:35,164
- Thank you.
- And secondly...

510
00:41:35,326 --> 00:41:37,875
...I'd like to give you something.

511
00:41:38,788 --> 00:41:41,007
You know, dreams do come true.

512
00:41:45,837 --> 00:41:48,215
Oh, my God.

513
00:41:50,258 --> 00:41:52,636
- Levi!
- Trying to take my girl?

514
00:41:56,556 --> 00:41:58,103
Get off me.

515
00:41:58,766 --> 00:42:00,439
Let me have him!

516
00:42:01,060 --> 00:42:03,529
- Come on, Levi.
- What's wrong with you, Negro?

517
00:42:03,688 --> 00:42:07,238
Take me at least 30 minutes
to get my hair like this.

518
00:42:08,234 --> 00:42:10,953
It's gonna get messed up
tonight anyway.

519
00:42:13,448 --> 00:42:17,373
I'm sorry, sisters. I'm gonna go outside
and be waiting on you.

520
00:42:25,835 --> 00:42:28,964
Oh, my God.

521
00:42:29,130 --> 00:42:30,882
How could you do that to Levi?

522
00:42:31,049 --> 00:42:33,302
Oh, Levi's a grown man.
He can handle himself.

523
00:42:33,468 --> 00:42:36,096
Don't listen to her.
She's damn near 30 and not married.

524
00:42:36,262 --> 00:42:38,060
- Shut up.
- You shut up.

525
00:42:38,222 --> 00:42:39,519
But Levi loves you.

526
00:42:40,433 --> 00:42:45,360
Spark, when you see a train that's gonna
get you to where you're trying to go...

527
00:42:45,521 --> 00:42:47,615
...you can't wait to live.

528
00:42:47,774 --> 00:42:49,822
You gotta jump on it.

529
00:42:49,984 --> 00:42:51,782
He ain't got nothing else on me.

530
00:42:51,944 --> 00:42:54,823
What he got?
More money? Better clothes?

531
00:42:54,989 --> 00:42:56,957
What else he got?
He got nothing on me.

532
00:42:57,116 --> 00:42:59,118
But she ain't worth it.
He ain't worth it.

533
00:42:59,285 --> 00:43:01,754
- You my family. I'm your blood.
- Then act like it!

534
00:43:01,913 --> 00:43:04,132
- Act like you're my blood!
- Hey.

535
00:43:05,291 --> 00:43:09,296
If not for more than the drool that you
deposit on my couch every single night...

536
00:43:09,462 --> 00:43:11,965
-...you should have had my back.
- I did have your back.

537
00:43:12,131 --> 00:43:13,474
No, you didn't.

538
00:43:13,633 --> 00:43:18,480
- You didn't have my back.
- Oh, coz.

539
00:43:18,638 --> 00:43:20,857
<i>It's business.</i>

540
00:43:22,433 --> 00:43:23,480
It's just business.

541
00:43:30,149 --> 00:43:32,277
Levi, where you going?

542
00:43:34,529 --> 00:43:38,250
Levi, it ain't personal.

543
00:43:39,700 --> 00:43:42,078
Just business, right?

544
00:43:53,005 --> 00:43:55,349
Mercy, mercy, mercy!

545
00:43:55,842 --> 00:43:58,641
Let's get this food out here,
Miss Emma.

546
00:43:59,804 --> 00:44:02,227
The Lord loves good-smelling food.

547
00:44:02,390 --> 00:44:04,188
Smells so good, Mama.

548
00:44:04,350 --> 00:44:06,569
- Thank you, baby.
- Delicious.

549
00:44:07,520 --> 00:44:10,239
Okay. Reverend,
will you bless the food, please?

550
00:44:10,398 --> 00:44:12,617
Sister's not here yet.
She said she was coming.

551
00:44:12,775 --> 00:44:16,496
Sparkle, those who do, do, baby.

552
00:44:16,904 --> 00:44:18,781
Pastor, thank you.

553
00:44:18,948 --> 00:44:20,746
Please, bow our heads.

554
00:44:20,908 --> 00:44:22,376
Our Father in heaven...

555
00:44:22,535 --> 00:44:25,709
...for this meal you have given,
we want to say thank you.

556
00:44:26,247 --> 00:44:29,342
And...bless the ones who prepared it.

557
00:44:29,500 --> 00:44:32,629
And, Lord, as we share it,
will you stay with us...

558
00:44:32,795 --> 00:44:34,172
...and be our guest of honor?

559
00:44:34,338 --> 00:44:38,218
But not just at this meal,
but God in our waking...

560
00:44:38,384 --> 00:44:41,809
...God in our speaking,
God in our playing...

561
00:44:41,971 --> 00:44:43,564
...God in our digesting...

562
00:44:43,723 --> 00:44:47,728
...God in our working,
God in our resting.

563
00:44:47,894 --> 00:44:49,896
In a world where so many are lonely...

564
00:44:50,062 --> 00:44:54,158
...may we share this friendship
with joyful hearts.

565
00:44:54,317 --> 00:44:59,414
- Amen.
- May this food, so fresh and fragrant...

566
00:44:59,572 --> 00:45:03,452
...call forth reverence for you
in our souls.

567
00:45:03,618 --> 00:45:06,963
As you give this strength
to our perishable limbs...

568
00:45:07,121 --> 00:45:10,216
...so give us grace
for our immortal lives.

569
00:45:10,374 --> 00:45:14,049
And let's not forget the blessings
on this family, Father God.

570
00:45:14,212 --> 00:45:17,682
Lord, we thank you. Amen.

571
00:45:17,840 --> 00:45:19,012
Amen!

572
00:45:19,175 --> 00:45:21,894
Now, that's why black folks
can't get ahead, right there.

573
00:45:22,428 --> 00:45:23,771
Not because we lazy.

574
00:45:23,930 --> 00:45:26,900
It's because we're too busy praying
over 40 acres and a mule.

575
00:45:27,058 --> 00:45:29,106
Now, by the time
black folks get to "amen"...

576
00:45:29,268 --> 00:45:31,270
...the mule is dog food...

577
00:45:31,437 --> 00:45:35,032
...and the 40 acres is sold
from underneath us.

578
00:45:35,191 --> 00:45:36,613
Because we too busy praying.

579
00:45:38,986 --> 00:45:41,614
Mom, this is Satin.

580
00:45:42,448 --> 00:45:45,247
- Pleasure.
- Pleasure is mine, all mine.

581
00:45:50,623 --> 00:45:52,717
Two dollars say
he doesn't make it to dessert.

582
00:45:52,875 --> 00:45:55,799
Five says he doesn't get food on his plate.
Look at Mama's face.

583
00:45:56,504 --> 00:45:58,381
- This is Mrs. Waters.
- Pleasure.

584
00:45:58,547 --> 00:46:00,220
- And Tune Ann.
- Hey, Tune Ann.

585
00:46:01,008 --> 00:46:02,055
- My sisters.
- Hey.

586
00:46:02,218 --> 00:46:04,641
And this is the Reverend Bryce.

587
00:46:04,804 --> 00:46:07,023
What do you say, Rev?

588
00:46:07,181 --> 00:46:08,478
Satin Struthers.

589
00:46:08,641 --> 00:46:11,360
Yeah, yeah, I seen you on TV.

590
00:46:11,519 --> 00:46:14,568
You were pretty hard
on the folk in Detroit after the riots.

591
00:46:15,648 --> 00:46:19,152
Well, I was telling the truth, you know.
It shows a lack of intelligence...

592
00:46:19,318 --> 00:46:21,491
...for someone to loot
their own neighborhood.

593
00:46:21,654 --> 00:46:22,951
Well, people were angry.

594
00:46:23,114 --> 00:46:24,991
At white people.

595
00:46:25,157 --> 00:46:27,626
- Hell, go tear up they shit.
- What--?

596
00:46:29,328 --> 00:46:31,251
Definitely not making it to dessert.

597
00:46:31,414 --> 00:46:34,463
Excuse me. I'm sorry. Hail Mary.

598
00:46:35,668 --> 00:46:36,715
That's Catholic.

599
00:46:37,295 --> 00:46:38,672
It's still Christian, right?

600
00:46:39,171 --> 00:46:42,516
I mean, come on.
I understand, I understand.

601
00:46:42,675 --> 00:46:46,054
I was trying to get black people
to see it from a different perspective.

602
00:46:46,220 --> 00:46:49,474
Burning and looting your own
neighborhood may be misguided...

603
00:46:50,182 --> 00:46:54,062
...but at least those people out there
were trying to fight to change the system.

604
00:46:54,228 --> 00:46:56,026
Now, with all due respect...

605
00:46:56,188 --> 00:46:59,943
...you just trying to
make a dollar off their pain.

606
00:47:01,360 --> 00:47:05,365
I bet you know a little bit more about
making dollars off of people's pain.

607
00:47:05,531 --> 00:47:07,408
You packing them
into church every Sunday.

608
00:47:07,575 --> 00:47:10,374
Giving them a show,
got them hooting and hollering. Yeah.

609
00:47:10,536 --> 00:47:11,583
You know what, Rev?

610
00:47:11,746 --> 00:47:13,794
The only difference
between me and you...

611
00:47:13,956 --> 00:47:17,005
...is you collect your fee at the pew...

612
00:47:17,168 --> 00:47:19,170
...I collect mine at the door.

613
00:47:27,887 --> 00:47:30,060
Well, Ms. Anderson...

614
00:47:31,349 --> 00:47:34,068
...I guess now is a good time
for me to let you know...

615
00:47:34,226 --> 00:47:37,571
...that I asked your daughter
to marry me.

616
00:47:39,732 --> 00:47:41,405
Surprise.

617
00:47:42,318 --> 00:47:43,661
He asked me last night.

618
00:47:43,819 --> 00:47:47,699
Got down on one knee and told me
that he couldn't live without me.

619
00:47:47,865 --> 00:47:52,917
Sister, you're going to marry this man?

620
00:47:53,079 --> 00:47:57,676
He disrespects our home,
the reverend.

621
00:47:57,833 --> 00:48:00,757
Oh, he's a comedian.
He was just trying to make us laugh.

622
00:48:01,295 --> 00:48:03,673
He's a really good man.

623
00:48:03,839 --> 00:48:05,841
Even goes to church sometimes.

624
00:48:06,008 --> 00:48:09,763
Granted, it is for material,
but I am there...

625
00:48:09,929 --> 00:48:11,431
-...and God knows my heart.
- Stop.

626
00:48:11,597 --> 00:48:13,224
- I got a good heart.
- Stop.

627
00:48:13,391 --> 00:48:15,393
He tithes.

628
00:48:18,479 --> 00:48:21,449
Child, I think enough of you
to introduce you...

629
00:48:21,607 --> 00:48:25,453
...to dentists and doctors
and accountants.

630
00:48:25,611 --> 00:48:28,410
But, no, not you.

631
00:48:28,572 --> 00:48:30,119
You want to whore with this coon.

632
00:48:30,282 --> 00:48:32,205
- Mom!
- Sparkle.

633
00:48:36,747 --> 00:48:40,593
Ms. Anderson,
I'm probably more of a Sambo.

634
00:48:43,212 --> 00:48:48,389
I coon from time to time,
but Sambo's my go-to.

635
00:48:50,719 --> 00:48:54,519
Baby, think more of yourself.

636
00:48:54,682 --> 00:48:59,984
I know you're worried about getting older
and who's gonna marry you.

637
00:49:00,146 --> 00:49:01,864
But get older, not desperate!

638
00:49:02,022 --> 00:49:03,990
Desperate?

639
00:49:05,317 --> 00:49:07,661
I'm doing a whole lot better
than you ever did.

640
00:49:08,529 --> 00:49:11,453
Just keeping a man
is a whole lot better than you ever did.

641
00:49:11,615 --> 00:49:13,993
- Ladies, please. I think--
- No, no, no, Reverend.

642
00:49:14,160 --> 00:49:16,629
Let her get her attention.
She doesn't have much else.

643
00:49:17,121 --> 00:49:20,921
- Maybe this is a conversation--
- Me getting a husband is not about me.

644
00:49:21,083 --> 00:49:24,804
It's about her. It's not my fault
that she got knocked up at 16...

645
00:49:25,045 --> 00:49:27,969
...and is trying to convince folks
she's the perfect mother...

646
00:49:28,132 --> 00:49:31,682
...raised some good girls.
Sparkle's gonna follow up behind you...

647
00:49:31,844 --> 00:49:34,848
...and be a little church mouse
and make dresses.

648
00:49:35,014 --> 00:49:37,267
And if she's lucky,
she'll be a preacher's wife.

649
00:49:37,433 --> 00:49:41,563
Dee's gonna be a doctor,
and I'm just supposed to marry one?

650
00:49:41,729 --> 00:49:44,403
Funny thing is,
maybe I could have snagged one...

651
00:49:44,565 --> 00:49:46,818
...if you'd sent me to school
like these two.

652
00:49:46,984 --> 00:49:49,988
But instead, I was at home,
raising your kids...

653
00:49:50,154 --> 00:49:52,156
...while you were laid up
in your own vomit.

654
00:49:52,323 --> 00:49:54,166
Sister...

655
00:49:54,325 --> 00:49:56,953
...if you gonna tell my tragic story...

656
00:49:57,119 --> 00:50:00,123
...give me the honor
of getting it correct.

657
00:50:00,331 --> 00:50:02,299
Yeah, I passed out a few times.

658
00:50:02,458 --> 00:50:05,086
Sure, I've had my moments.

659
00:50:05,252 --> 00:50:11,760
But you've never, ever, ever
seen me laying in my own vomit.

660
00:50:12,176 --> 00:50:13,553
Whatever you say, Mama.

661
00:50:15,095 --> 00:50:19,942
The fact is, I was desperate back then.

662
00:50:20,100 --> 00:50:22,398
Right now,
I'm trying to get myself out of here...

663
00:50:22,561 --> 00:50:25,565
...and get myself more than
a color TV and half a room.

664
00:50:25,731 --> 00:50:27,028
It's okay.

665
00:50:35,407 --> 00:50:37,501
Well, we better go.

666
00:50:37,660 --> 00:50:41,710
Ms. Anderson, thanks for what looked like
could have been a great dinner.

667
00:50:44,291 --> 00:50:45,338
We better go.

668
00:50:48,754 --> 00:50:50,677
Sister!

669
00:50:50,839 --> 00:50:55,595
You leave my house,
there's no coming back.

670
00:50:56,679 --> 00:50:57,896
Not this time.

671
00:51:08,941 --> 00:51:12,411
Sparkle. Sparkle!

672
00:51:20,995 --> 00:51:23,168
Are you still gonna be
part of the group?

673
00:51:24,456 --> 00:51:28,461
That's not exactly
what was on my mind, Spark.

674
00:51:28,627 --> 00:51:30,504
Yeah, sure.

675
00:51:40,055 --> 00:51:42,103
Dee, say something.

676
00:51:45,477 --> 00:51:46,569
Congratulations.

677
00:51:48,105 --> 00:51:49,982
Thank you.

678
00:51:51,525 --> 00:51:52,572
Thank you.

679
00:51:57,197 --> 00:51:59,074
Come here.

680
00:52:01,243 --> 00:52:02,586
I love you, Spark.

681
00:52:05,706 --> 00:52:07,629
It's okay.

682
00:52:57,800 --> 00:52:59,928
Where you want to go?

683
00:53:00,094 --> 00:53:01,812
Anywhere.

684
00:53:24,159 --> 00:53:26,332
Close your eyes.

685
00:53:35,170 --> 00:53:39,346
Okay, you can open them.

686
00:53:40,092 --> 00:53:42,515
Your cup of coffee, sir.

687
00:53:45,723 --> 00:53:47,441
I appreciate it, baby.

688
00:53:47,599 --> 00:53:51,320
You know, Daddy got to wake up
a little faster and a little stronger.

689
00:53:51,478 --> 00:53:55,483
You'll be surprised with
what this gonna do when we make love.

690
00:53:57,818 --> 00:54:01,243
Can't be any better than it already is.

691
00:54:24,303 --> 00:54:26,476
- Are you catching a cold?
- No, I'm fine.

692
00:54:26,638 --> 00:54:28,891
Okay, from "You bring out
the woman in me."

693
00:54:29,057 --> 00:54:30,934
Five, six, seven, eight.

694
00:54:36,064 --> 00:54:37,782
Can you not hit my hand every time?

695
00:54:37,941 --> 00:54:41,115
Okay, come on, come on.
Five, six, seven, eight.

696
00:54:45,491 --> 00:54:48,165
Y'all ain't got to go home...

697
00:54:48,327 --> 00:54:49,499
...but you know the rest.

698
00:54:51,246 --> 00:54:54,341
Oh, they were just leaving.

699
00:54:54,500 --> 00:54:56,218
Baby, you got some
cab fare for them?

700
00:54:56,376 --> 00:54:58,253
Cab fare?

701
00:54:58,837 --> 00:55:00,680
You the one opening for
Aretha Franklin.

702
00:55:02,049 --> 00:55:05,428
I mean, hell, if I had any sense,
I'd be living off your ass.

703
00:55:08,388 --> 00:55:11,517
- I'm funny, Sparkle? I'm funny?
- Yeah.

704
00:55:11,683 --> 00:55:14,778
So you laughing at me
like them white folks that I coon for?

705
00:55:16,480 --> 00:55:17,527
- No.
- Satin.

706
00:55:17,689 --> 00:55:19,987
Well, you should.

707
00:55:20,150 --> 00:55:22,824
That's how I'm paying
for all this heat you sucking up.

708
00:55:22,986 --> 00:55:25,455
- Satin, I'm just--
- Let's just go. Come on, just go.

709
00:55:25,614 --> 00:55:27,161
Grab your book.

710
00:55:35,332 --> 00:55:36,549
Ready for TV, Ms. Sparkle?

711
00:55:36,708 --> 00:55:39,086
Oh, my God, Ms. Franklin!

712
00:55:39,253 --> 00:55:40,300
Hello.

713
00:55:40,462 --> 00:55:43,056
Today ain't the day
to be fashionably late.

714
00:55:43,215 --> 00:55:44,262
You're fine.

715
00:55:44,424 --> 00:55:46,802
Stix says Ms. Franklin's not here.
Running late.

716
00:55:47,302 --> 00:55:50,306
I'm worried because that's gonna
cut it close to us getting home.

717
00:55:50,472 --> 00:55:51,689
Sure is.

718
00:55:52,432 --> 00:55:54,150
Do you have any more pins?

719
00:55:54,309 --> 00:55:57,313
I'm running out of mine over here
and I need some more.

720
00:55:57,479 --> 00:55:59,732
I can't get this thing on.

721
00:56:01,066 --> 00:56:02,443
What happened to your face?

722
00:56:02,609 --> 00:56:04,737
Oh, it ain't nothing.

723
00:56:04,903 --> 00:56:06,530
He did that to you, didn't he?

724
00:56:06,697 --> 00:56:08,324
I had an accident.

725
00:56:08,490 --> 00:56:10,584
Oh, so, what,
you tripped and hit his fist?

726
00:56:10,742 --> 00:56:11,994
Get out.

727
00:56:12,744 --> 00:56:13,791
Excuse me?

728
00:56:14,538 --> 00:56:16,586
I told you to get out of my face.

729
00:56:16,748 --> 00:56:19,092
He's beating you,
and you're taking it out on me?

730
00:56:19,251 --> 00:56:22,050
- Just go. Go! Get out!
- No!

731
00:56:22,212 --> 00:56:24,385
I don't need to hear this.

732
00:56:25,549 --> 00:56:28,223
- Jeez, she's always in my business!
- Somebody ought to be!

733
